ZH: 这座祭坛是我们祖先留下来的文化遗产。
EN: This altar is a cultural heritage left by our ancestors.

ZH: 他们会在祭坛前祈祷祝福。
EN: They pray for blessings in front of the altar.

ZH: 这座祭坛是为了祭奠逝去的英雄而建立的。
EN: The altar was built to honor the fallen heroes.

ZH: 在节日里，人们会在祭坛前献上香火。
EN: People will offer incense at the altar during festivals.

ZH: 这座祭坛是用最高级的石材建造的。
EN: The altar is built with the finest stone.

ZH: 祭坛的神像非常庄严肃穆。
EN: The deity on the altar looks very solemn.

ZH: 祭坛上摆放着新鲜的花朵。
EN: Fresh flowers are placed on the altar.

ZH: 古代的祭坛通常用来祭祀神灵。
EN: Ancient altars were usually used to worship gods.

ZH: 祭坛上燃起了一团团的火焰。
EN: Flames are burning on the altar.

ZH: 祭坛上放着一尊金光闪闪的佛像。
EN: A shiny golden Buddha statue is placed on the altar.

ZH: 阳光透过玻璃窗照在祭坛上。
EN: The sunlight shines through the glass window onto the altar.

ZH: 祭坛的边缘雕刻着精美的花纹。
EN: The edges of the altar are carved with intricate patterns.

ZH: 祭坛前站着一群信徒在念经。
EN: A group of believers are chanting in front of the altar.

ZH: 祭坛的设计展现了古代建筑的魅力。
EN: The design of the altar showcases the charm of ancient architecture.

ZH: 祭坛上点燃了一根香。
EN: An incense stick is lit on the altar.

ZH: 祭坛上铺着一层纯白的布。
EN: A layer of pure white cloth is spread on the altar.

ZH: 他在祭坛前献上了虔诚的祈祷。
EN: He offered a devout prayer in front of the altar.

ZH: 祭坛的壁画描绘了历史上的一幕幕风景。
EN: The mural on the altar depicts scenes from history.

ZH: 祭坛上供奉着我国古代的名人像。
EN: The altar is dedicated to the portraits of famous figures in our ancient history.

ZH: 每逢农历的初一十五，村民们都会聚集在祭坛前祈福。
EN: On the first and fifteenth day of the lunar month, villagers gather in front of the altar to pray for blessings.
